<br>
Thus, the level limits are set low by MMORPG standards.  20th level characters are pretty godly, and (though I haven't been paying attention since WoTC took over) that's been the level limit in the AD&amp;D &gt; AD&amp;D2E &gt; D&amp;D3E games for over twenty years.<br>
<br>
Play a game like Baldur's Gate II and watch how quickly you can jack a character to maximum level as compared to, say, in EQ or any other MMORPG.<br>
<br>
D&amp;D's a great, fun face-to-face system but I don't think it'd work for MMORPGs.<br>
<br>
Such a shame, as there are thirty years of wonderful settings to work with. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=maladominus>Maladominus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ak'Anon Sex Symbol</span><br>  Posts: 1144<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/24/03 6:17:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1471.topic&index=31>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: D'oh!</span><hr size=1> D&amp;D for MMORPG?  <br>
