<br>
Corporate or otherwise,we're all under the NDA-no discussion allowed,no matter what part of the company you're in.<br>
 <br>
Though I will say with 3.5 coming, any online project would have to be retooled. A lot of &quot;core&quot; spells,for example have been revamped (see the most recent issue of Dragon for examples). This means even Neverwinter Nights no longer is quite accurate,since haste,hold,and polymorph effects have been altered.... <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
 <br>
Further,a LOT of the old campaigns actually aren't under the control of Wizards! Ravenloft is actually a -White Wolf- project...some of my friends actually work on supplements,and a whole pack of characters from the LARP I play have Ravenloft equivalents in same. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
 <br>
Heck,a lot of what people consider &quot;Wizards&quot; product isn't. Dragon and Dungeon magazines,for example-they're run by ex-WoTC employees,who own them...as independant magazines.<br>
